1
00:02:03,200 --> 00:02:05,640
<i>I've come to see Bandit Wad.</i>
<i>I have something urgent to discuss.</i>

2
00:02:05,720 --> 00:02:08,000
- Kill him!
- <i>Anitassa na appati</i>

3
00:02:09,000 --> 00:02:11,360
<i>The new governor</i>
<i>caught Bandit Yai and his men</i>

4
00:02:11,440 --> 00:02:12,840
<i>and ordered them hanged immediately.</i>

5
00:02:12,920 --> 00:02:14,480
Why so suddenly?

6
00:02:14,560 --> 00:02:17,000
The governor of Tha Khiri
won't let my father and me go.

7
00:02:17,080 --> 00:02:18,760
I'll come get you
at the forest edge by the foothills.

8
00:02:18,840 --> 00:02:20,040
Thanks, Wad.

9
00:02:20,120 --> 00:02:22,600
<i>Maybe they've been friends</i>
<i>since their days at Khao Phrom.</i>

10
00:02:22,680 --> 00:02:24,440
<i>I want to learn sorcery with you.</i>

11
00:02:24,520 --> 00:02:26,360
I'll hand you over to the governor.

12
00:02:26,440 --> 00:02:28,720
- <i>What happened?</i>
- <i>Chum betrayed us.</i>

13
00:02:28,800 --> 00:02:30,080
He used black dog's blood
to break the spell.

14
00:02:30,160 --> 00:02:33,200
From this day on, you and I are finished.

15
00:02:33,280 --> 00:02:36,760
<i>So where did your heart go to?</i>
<i>Was it that young man who bought you</i>

16
00:02:36,840 --> 00:02:38,120
<i>the human-faced bead bracelet?</i>

17
00:02:38,200 --> 00:02:40,920
<i>Why wouldn't I know?</i>
<i>I can tell you're in love.</i>

18
00:02:41,000 --> 00:02:44,360
I'll run away and live with you, Blur.

19
00:03:04,200 --> 00:03:05,120
Are you sure about this?

20
00:03:10,000 --> 00:03:11,080
Pud!

21
00:03:16,040 --> 00:03:16,880
Easy.

22
00:03:20,720 --> 00:03:22,800
I just want to talk.

23
00:03:24,160 --> 00:03:25,840
I have nothing to say to you.

24
00:03:30,120 --> 00:03:31,560
I heard

25
00:03:31,640 --> 00:03:34,280
you want to become a disciple
at Khao Phrom, don't you?

26
00:03:35,960 --> 00:03:37,640
I can help you.

27
00:03:37,720 --> 00:03:38,760
Alright?

28
00:03:40,160 --> 00:03:42,280
Brother, he's tricked us before.

29
00:03:42,880 --> 00:03:44,120
Don't believe him.

30
00:03:46,920 --> 00:03:49,680
I'm serious. I'm not lying.

31
00:03:50,320 --> 00:03:52,600
I swear on my honor as Bandit Pud.

32
00:03:53,280 --> 00:03:54,880
But if you're not interested,

33
00:03:55,840 --> 00:03:57,680
- I'll leave.
- Wait.

34
00:04:01,520 --> 00:04:02,880
Someone like Bandit Pud

35
00:04:03,680 --> 00:04:05,440
never helps anyone for free.

36
00:04:11,520 --> 00:04:14,080
I help you, you help me.

37
00:04:14,160 --> 00:04:15,720
Simple as that.

38
00:04:21,120 --> 00:04:22,280
What do you want me to do?

39
00:04:23,680 --> 00:04:24,520
Lasor.

40
00:04:26,560 --> 00:04:28,920
Khun Yod attacked Phraya Decha,

41
00:04:29,560 --> 00:04:31,640
the governor of Tha Khiri.
He's badly injured.

42
00:04:32,360 --> 00:04:34,880
If you help me capture him
and hand him over to the authorities,

43
00:04:35,640 --> 00:04:37,720
you'll earn merit and recognition.

44
00:04:38,400 --> 00:04:39,520
Then I'll tell the governor

45
00:04:40,240 --> 00:04:43,080
to send you to Khao Phrom immediately.

46
00:04:52,240 --> 00:04:55,520
So all I have to do is arrest Khun Yod
and hand him over?

47
00:04:58,520 --> 00:04:59,520
Yes.

48
00:05:00,760 --> 00:05:03,920
And you'll become a disciple
at Khao Phrom, just like you want.

49
00:05:08,400 --> 00:05:09,360
Yeah.

50
00:05:10,400 --> 00:05:11,760
This is the only way

51
00:05:12,400 --> 00:05:14,480
I'll ever get to study sorcery
at Khao Phrom.

52
00:05:16,360 --> 00:05:19,960
But Khun Yod is close friends
with Father Wad.

53
00:05:22,960 --> 00:05:24,320
Are you sure about this?

54
00:05:29,400 --> 00:05:30,600
Anyone who breaks the law

55
00:05:30,680 --> 00:05:33,040
must be investigated.

56
00:05:33,120 --> 00:05:35,080
If Khun Yod is innocent,

57
00:05:35,160 --> 00:05:36,640
they will release him.

58
00:05:37,200 --> 00:05:40,080
Brother, Bandit Pud betrayed us before.

59
00:05:41,240 --> 00:05:42,920
Can he really be trusted?

60
00:05:50,480 --> 00:05:51,960
I have no other choice.

61
00:05:53,440 --> 00:05:55,160
I have to risk it one more time.

62
00:06:21,360 --> 00:06:22,760
Pud!

63
00:06:22,840 --> 00:06:24,400
That bastard Pud must've fooled us.

64
00:06:34,640 --> 00:06:35,480
Hurry!

65
00:06:37,560 --> 00:06:39,280
Are you sure
blinding the Buddha will work?

66
00:06:40,040 --> 00:06:42,000
I trust my instincts.

67
00:06:59,560 --> 00:07:01,480
The entrance is open.

68
00:07:02,000 --> 00:07:03,320
Pud didn't trick us.

69
00:07:03,840 --> 00:07:05,440
He blinded the Buddha on the mountain.

70
00:07:06,120 --> 00:07:09,320
- Fire the flare. Signal them, now.
- Yes, sir.

71
00:07:11,400 --> 00:07:13,280
Men, attack!

72
00:07:22,120 --> 00:07:24,920
Bandit Wad's den is finished this time.

73
00:07:26,320 --> 00:07:28,960
Tim must be attacking already.
Should we go help them?

74
00:07:29,040 --> 00:07:29,960
No.

75
00:07:31,280 --> 00:07:32,680
I've got a bigger job.

76
00:07:44,440 --> 00:07:45,280
Where is Yiwha?

77
00:07:54,000 --> 00:07:55,120
Wad, we're in trouble.

78
00:07:55,200 --> 00:07:56,880
The governor's men are raiding Chum Suea.

79
00:07:57,960 --> 00:07:59,480
Niem, bring everyone with me.

80
00:08:00,080 --> 00:08:01,000
Let's go.

81
00:08:22,640 --> 00:08:23,680
Chum Suea!

82
00:08:24,480 --> 00:08:25,320
Dad!

83
00:09:14,160 --> 00:09:16,200
<i>U ami masa namo.</i>

84
00:09:28,800 --> 00:09:30,120
You know magic, don't you?

85
00:09:46,240 --> 00:09:48,000
- Niem.
- Yes?

86
00:09:48,080 --> 00:09:49,880
Get the women,
the elderly, and the children out.

87
00:09:50,400 --> 00:09:51,400
What about you?

88
00:09:52,000 --> 00:09:53,160
I'll hold them off.

89
00:09:53,240 --> 00:09:54,080
Go.

90
00:09:54,680 --> 00:09:55,840
Be careful, Wad.

91
00:09:59,200 --> 00:10:00,720
So tough-skinned, huh?

92
00:10:10,800 --> 00:10:11,760
Khun Paeng.

93
00:10:12,600 --> 00:10:14,200
Bandit Wad,

94
00:10:14,280 --> 00:10:15,760
if I kill you,

95
00:10:16,280 --> 00:10:18,680
the title of Luang Yokkrabat is mine.

96
00:10:20,040 --> 00:10:21,240
A backstabber like you?

97
00:10:21,920 --> 00:10:23,440
Don't dream too big.

98
00:10:23,960 --> 00:10:27,520
You're about to die
and you're still talking big. Let's see…

99
00:10:28,400 --> 00:10:31,200
with a bullet soaked in menstrual blood,

100
00:10:32,960 --> 00:10:34,640
will you still be so tough?

101
00:10:40,280 --> 00:10:42,760
<i>U ami masa namo.</i>

102
00:10:46,680 --> 00:10:47,680
Bandit Wad!

103
00:10:48,360 --> 00:10:49,320
Damn it!

104
00:10:52,040 --> 00:10:53,840
Burn Chum Suea to the ground!

105
00:10:53,920 --> 00:10:55,560
Kill them all.

106
00:10:56,200 --> 00:10:57,080
Go!

107
00:10:57,160 --> 00:10:59,680
Let's go!

108
00:11:22,240 --> 00:11:23,120
Uncle Niem!

109
00:11:25,040 --> 00:11:25,920
Who?

110
00:11:26,000 --> 00:11:27,800
Who did this to Chum Suea?

111
00:11:28,520 --> 00:11:30,480
Tim. The governor of Tha Khiri's men.

112
00:11:35,080 --> 00:11:37,280
What about Dad? Is he safe?

113
00:11:37,360 --> 00:11:39,800
Don't say anything right now.
Follow me first.

114
00:11:54,840 --> 00:11:56,120
Can't we rest for a moment?

115
00:11:56,720 --> 00:11:59,600
Yam's fever is rising.
I need to make her medicine.

116
00:12:01,240 --> 00:12:02,160
Hang in there.

117
00:12:03,160 --> 00:12:05,800
Once we're out of Khuan Phra-ngam,
your brother will make medicine for you.

118
00:12:15,440 --> 00:12:16,680
Yiam…

119
00:12:19,720 --> 00:12:22,800
Can you tell me
the story of Phra Aphai Mani?

120
00:12:23,760 --> 00:12:24,600
Of course.

121
00:12:25,160 --> 00:12:27,400
If you want to hear it, I'll tell you.

122
00:12:31,160 --> 00:12:36,240
He wails in longing,
lamenting in song, his heart desolate,

123
00:12:37,080 --> 00:12:41,160
making one think of home,
yearning, hoping still.

124
00:12:41,240 --> 00:12:45,120
To leave one's house
is like a bird that leaves its nest.

125
00:12:45,200 --> 00:12:49,320
It keeps looking back,
craning its neck, waiting.

126
00:13:36,440 --> 00:13:37,400
They're coming.

127
00:13:42,040 --> 00:13:43,320
You're ready, right?

128
00:13:48,000 --> 00:13:48,880
Yes.

129
00:13:55,800 --> 00:13:59,920
<i>A wich su nutsa nus ti.</i>

130
00:14:20,080 --> 00:14:21,600
You look exactly like Bandit Wad.

131
00:14:22,480 --> 00:14:26,400
The Narai transformation spell.
I'll teach it to you later, Lasor.

132
00:14:26,920 --> 00:14:28,160
Why are you pretending to be my father?

133
00:14:28,240 --> 00:14:29,400
Hey.

134
00:14:31,480 --> 00:14:33,000
A friend talking to a friend.

135
00:14:33,080 --> 00:14:34,960
It's easier that way.

136
00:14:35,040 --> 00:14:36,760
What friend?

137
00:14:37,480 --> 00:14:39,080
Lasor!

138
00:14:40,080 --> 00:14:41,480
Let me go.

139
00:14:46,920 --> 00:14:47,920
You.

140
00:14:48,600 --> 00:14:49,760
Go.

141
00:14:54,000 --> 00:14:55,120
Lasor!

142
00:14:55,200 --> 00:14:56,120
Don't believe him!

143
00:14:56,840 --> 00:14:58,360
He's tricking you!

144
00:14:58,440 --> 00:14:59,640
Don't believe him!

145
00:15:03,080 --> 00:15:04,400
Shut up.

146
00:15:22,080 --> 00:15:23,120
Who is he, Dad?

147
00:15:24,760 --> 00:15:26,320
Bandit Wad's son.

148
00:15:29,080 --> 00:15:30,080
Where's your father?

149
00:15:30,600 --> 00:15:31,960
I'm right here.

150
00:15:42,880 --> 00:15:43,800
That's all you brought?

151
00:15:47,760 --> 00:15:51,000
This is more than enough
to take you all the way.

152
00:16:00,520 --> 00:16:01,760
Wad, why did you kill him?!

153
00:16:03,920 --> 00:16:05,000
Mom!

154
00:16:11,400 --> 00:16:13,040
Mom! Yam!

155
00:16:13,120 --> 00:16:14,800
Yiam!

156
00:16:15,520 --> 00:16:16,600
Yiam.

157
00:16:18,280 --> 00:16:19,320
Mom!

158
00:16:21,000 --> 00:16:22,160
Tough bastard, aren't you?

159
00:16:28,040 --> 00:16:29,000
Yod.

160
00:16:31,040 --> 00:16:33,800
If you're about to drive those nails
into my guts,

161
00:16:36,880 --> 00:16:38,000
take a look over there.

162
00:16:39,040 --> 00:16:40,600
Yod!

163
00:16:40,680 --> 00:16:42,240
- Yod!
- Dad.

164
00:16:45,960 --> 00:16:47,120
Dad.

165
00:16:47,680 --> 00:16:49,120
- Dad.
- If you fight,

166
00:16:50,360 --> 00:16:52,240
I'll shoot them one by one.

167
00:16:52,320 --> 00:16:53,680
Yod!

168
00:16:54,840 --> 00:16:56,200
You bastard!

169
00:16:56,280 --> 00:16:57,360
Let my wife and children go!

170
00:16:57,440 --> 00:16:58,760
You want me to let them go?

171
00:16:58,840 --> 00:17:01,920
Then there has to be
an exchange, my friend.

172
00:17:02,000 --> 00:17:02,880
Yod!

173
00:17:03,480 --> 00:17:04,839
What do you want from me?

174
00:17:21,440 --> 00:17:23,920
That chest tattoo of yours.

175
00:17:25,920 --> 00:17:27,800
Master of Khao Phrom
gave it to you, right?

176
00:17:29,320 --> 00:17:30,520
I want it.

177
00:17:31,680 --> 00:17:34,160
Old Master Khrua Phut
would never tattoo a thief like you.

178
00:17:36,280 --> 00:17:39,200
That's why I had to come
begging you myself.

179
00:17:42,080 --> 00:17:43,960
- Yod!
- Dad!

180
00:17:53,320 --> 00:17:54,320
What are you going to do?

181
00:17:58,640 --> 00:18:00,920
I'm going to skin you

182
00:18:01,720 --> 00:18:03,640
and make a tattooed jacket out of it.

183
00:18:05,600 --> 00:18:07,480
I can't help.

184
00:18:07,560 --> 00:18:10,320
You're damn invulnerable.
Can't cut you. Can't stab you.

185
00:18:10,400 --> 00:18:12,920
Poor Yod…

186
00:18:13,000 --> 00:18:14,600
This time,

187
00:18:15,960 --> 00:18:18,280
you'll have to endure a little pain.

188
00:18:26,320 --> 00:18:27,360
Lasor.

189
00:18:32,960 --> 00:18:34,800
Stab his anus.

190
00:18:34,880 --> 00:18:36,560
You damned wretch!

191
00:18:39,080 --> 00:18:41,000
- Dad.
- Yod.

192
00:18:41,600 --> 00:18:42,720
- Yod.
- Dad.

193
00:18:54,120 --> 00:18:55,360
Does it hurt?

194
00:18:57,920 --> 00:18:58,760
Mom.

195
00:18:58,840 --> 00:19:00,520
I told you to stab his anus!

196
00:19:02,640 --> 00:19:03,560
Stab!

197
00:19:13,360 --> 00:19:16,640
No. Mom.

198
00:19:22,280 --> 00:19:23,600
No!

199
00:19:26,360 --> 00:19:28,000
Dad!

200
00:19:28,080 --> 00:19:31,040
Dad!

201
00:19:31,120 --> 00:19:32,160
Dad!

202
00:19:52,920 --> 00:19:54,520
You hellish beast!

203
00:19:54,600 --> 00:19:56,040
I'll kill you!

204
00:20:09,240 --> 00:20:10,080
Hey.

205
00:20:17,760 --> 00:20:19,440
Yam! Mom!

206
00:20:34,760 --> 00:20:35,760
Dad!

207
00:20:41,960 --> 00:20:43,200
Let me go!

208
00:21:54,360 --> 00:21:56,000
Throw the bodies into the ravine.

209
00:22:06,040 --> 00:22:07,640
You're shaking like a baby bird.

210
00:22:07,720 --> 00:22:09,120
Why did you kill Khun Yod?

211
00:22:11,600 --> 00:22:12,480
I didn't.

212
00:22:13,160 --> 00:22:14,840
You did.

213
00:22:17,640 --> 00:22:18,880
What do you mean?

214
00:22:20,120 --> 00:22:21,960
- Hey! There they are!
- Retreat.

215
00:22:33,480 --> 00:22:34,760
Let me go!

216
00:22:36,720 --> 00:22:38,440
- Take him to the police station.
- Yes, sir.

217
00:22:38,520 --> 00:22:40,320
I didn't do it!

218
00:22:41,280 --> 00:22:43,680
Let me go! I didn't do it!

219
00:22:43,760 --> 00:22:45,360
You think you're tough? Go.

220
00:22:46,120 --> 00:22:47,600
Go!

221
00:23:01,080 --> 00:23:02,320
Do you think he's dead?

222
00:23:02,920 --> 00:23:03,920
Just throw him down.

223
00:23:04,000 --> 00:23:05,280
He won't survive anyway.

224
00:23:05,800 --> 00:23:06,960
Come on.

225
00:23:30,920 --> 00:23:31,840
Yod…

226
00:23:40,080 --> 00:23:41,480
Forgive me, Yod.

227
00:23:44,120 --> 00:23:45,360
I came too late.

228
00:23:48,160 --> 00:23:50,200
I couldn't save you or your family.

229
00:23:51,040 --> 00:23:52,080
Yod…

230
00:24:38,120 --> 00:24:41,280
PATROL UNIT

231
00:24:46,680 --> 00:24:49,640
Let me go! Hey!

232
00:24:49,720 --> 00:24:51,080
Let me go!

233
00:24:53,400 --> 00:24:54,840
Announce it.

234
00:24:54,920 --> 00:24:57,080
Bandit Wad and his son

235
00:24:57,160 --> 00:25:00,680
slaughtered the entire household
of Village Chief Khun Yod Pakdee.

236
00:25:00,760 --> 00:25:03,640
I didn't do it!
I didn't kill Khun Yod Pakdee!

237
00:25:03,720 --> 00:25:05,360
Caught red-handed

238
00:25:05,440 --> 00:25:07,800
and you still deny it, Lasor?

239
00:25:07,880 --> 00:25:10,440
I told you I didn't do it!

240
00:25:11,480 --> 00:25:13,280
Everything that happened

241
00:25:13,360 --> 00:25:15,480
is because of your stupidity.

242
00:25:16,880 --> 00:25:20,120
Guard him well.
I'm reporting to the governor.

243
00:25:20,200 --> 00:25:22,080
Tomorrow,

244
00:25:22,160 --> 00:25:25,120
I'll come watch you hang, Lasor.

245
00:25:26,640 --> 00:25:28,760
I didn't do it! Let me go!

246
00:25:33,400 --> 00:25:34,320
Pud!

247
00:25:35,080 --> 00:25:37,320
I'll kill you.
You'll die in the most painful way.

248
00:25:44,080 --> 00:25:46,040
PATROL UNIT

249
00:26:19,280 --> 00:26:20,400
Fire!

250
00:26:20,480 --> 00:26:22,200
Fire!

251
00:26:22,280 --> 00:26:24,480
Hey! I'm in here! Let me out!

252
00:26:24,560 --> 00:26:25,520
Let me out!

253
00:26:26,720 --> 00:26:28,680
- Nui.
- Lasor.

254
00:26:30,680 --> 00:26:33,200
The keys. Behind you. On the table.

255
00:26:33,280 --> 00:26:34,680
Do you see them? On the table.

256
00:26:35,720 --> 00:26:36,680
Got it.

257
00:26:39,880 --> 00:26:40,960
Not this one.

258
00:26:43,840 --> 00:26:45,240
- Got it.
- Hurry!

259
00:26:48,720 --> 00:26:49,720
Thank you.

260
00:26:49,800 --> 00:26:51,120
No time for that. Let's run.

261
00:26:53,600 --> 00:26:54,520
This way.

262
00:27:27,280 --> 00:27:30,200
<i>Yiam, can you read Phra Aphai Mani to me?</i>

263
00:27:34,800 --> 00:27:37,800
Yiam, can you read Phra Aphai Mani to me?

264
00:27:43,840 --> 00:27:48,320
<i>"Suddenly rang the eerie chime</i>

265
00:27:48,400 --> 00:27:51,080
<i>A haunting sound</i>

266
00:27:51,720 --> 00:27:55,400
<i>That stirred the heart</i>

267
00:27:55,480 --> 00:27:58,120
<i>I turned and searched</i>

268
00:27:58,880 --> 00:28:05,040
<i>Behold, a hermit riding a rainbow</i>

269
00:28:05,640 --> 00:28:09,720
<i>Descending, guiding me</i>

270
00:28:09,800 --> 00:28:12,120
<i>To the mountaintop"</i>

271
00:28:48,920 --> 00:28:51,920
Someone came here
and covered the Buddha's head.

272
00:28:52,000 --> 00:28:53,840
That's how Tim's men broke in.

273
00:28:54,520 --> 00:28:56,240
Just like Lasor said.

274
00:28:56,800 --> 00:28:59,400
It must've been Chum
who told them our secret.

275
00:29:03,360 --> 00:29:05,000
So many of us were shot dead.

276
00:29:06,160 --> 00:29:07,720
Those who survived are badly wounded.

277
00:29:14,360 --> 00:29:16,000
Poor Phon…

278
00:29:16,080 --> 00:29:17,840
She was alive just a moment ago.

279
00:29:18,760 --> 00:29:21,000
Our people did not die for nothing.

280
00:29:22,720 --> 00:29:23,760
Dad.

281
00:29:28,760 --> 00:29:29,720
I, Bandit Wad,

282
00:29:31,520 --> 00:29:34,960
swear to the people of Chum Suea,
both those who have died

283
00:29:35,720 --> 00:29:37,040
and those still alive,

284
00:29:39,000 --> 00:29:41,080
before this sacred image.

285
00:29:42,680 --> 00:29:44,600
Please bear witness

286
00:29:45,120 --> 00:29:46,480
that I, Bandit Wad,

287
00:29:46,560 --> 00:29:49,000
will take revenge
on those who did this to us,

288
00:29:50,640 --> 00:29:52,840
and repay them in full.

289
00:29:53,760 --> 00:29:54,920
An eye for an eye.

290
00:29:55,520 --> 00:29:56,760
A tooth for a tooth.

291
00:30:13,240 --> 00:30:17,040
Niem will take you south
to stay with Chaem at Huai Yao.

292
00:30:17,120 --> 00:30:20,320
Hide there until things calm down.

293
00:30:21,320 --> 00:30:22,760
What about you?

294
00:30:23,720 --> 00:30:25,040
I'll stay in Tha Khiri

295
00:30:26,080 --> 00:30:27,360
and wait for my chance.

296
00:30:29,280 --> 00:30:31,280
You can't fight them alone.

297
00:30:32,000 --> 00:30:33,280
Yod is already dead.

298
00:30:33,360 --> 00:30:36,400
If I don't behead them,
I'll never rest in peace.

299
00:30:41,840 --> 00:30:42,800
Dad,

300
00:30:45,960 --> 00:30:47,680
let's stop being bandits.

301
00:30:49,240 --> 00:30:51,440
Let's run away and start over together.

302
00:30:59,640 --> 00:31:00,480
Yiwha,

303
00:31:04,880 --> 00:31:06,400
you go start a new life.

304
00:31:08,680 --> 00:31:09,840
My life

305
00:31:11,240 --> 00:31:12,880
ended with Chum Suea.

306
00:31:14,800 --> 00:31:16,360
I don't want your hands
stained with blood anymore.

307
00:31:16,440 --> 00:31:17,680
And what about Yod's life?

308
00:31:17,760 --> 00:31:18,880
Ouam?

309
00:31:19,520 --> 00:31:20,880
Pho?

310
00:31:21,680 --> 00:31:22,640
Phon?

311
00:31:23,400 --> 00:31:25,560
My brothers and sisters,
my friends who have died?

312
00:31:26,640 --> 00:31:28,520
Should they die for nothing?

313
00:31:35,600 --> 00:31:36,840
I'll take care of Yiwha.

314
00:31:37,640 --> 00:31:38,840
Don't worry.

315
00:31:41,000 --> 00:31:42,200
I'm counting on you, Niem.

316
00:32:04,320 --> 00:32:06,760
Let's hurry before they come back.

317
00:32:15,040 --> 00:32:16,520
Let's go. There's no time.

318
00:32:21,840 --> 00:32:23,480
So damn satisfying!

319
00:32:26,320 --> 00:32:30,200
Let Wad and that Khun Yod
go to hell together.

320
00:32:31,280 --> 00:32:32,760
But Bandit Wad got away, Uncle.

321
00:32:33,800 --> 00:32:37,240
Let him run. Now he's a wanted man.

322
00:32:37,320 --> 00:32:40,400
The officials are hunting him everywhere.

323
00:32:43,080 --> 00:32:44,640
And if he comes back for revenge?

324
00:32:46,320 --> 00:32:48,200
Don't be stupid.

325
00:32:48,280 --> 00:32:50,960
Wad thinks
the governor sent men to raid him.

326
00:32:51,040 --> 00:32:52,360
He won't suspect me.

327
00:32:53,760 --> 00:32:56,160
And Khun Yod, the one you killed?

328
00:32:58,200 --> 00:33:01,160
I already made Lasor
and his father take the fall.

329
00:33:02,400 --> 00:33:06,280
As for me? I'm just waiting to collect
the reward money from the governor.

330
00:33:09,640 --> 00:33:11,280
You really are clever.

331
00:33:11,360 --> 00:33:14,360
Wicked beyond human,
like hell spat you out into this world.

332
00:33:14,440 --> 00:33:16,120
I'll kick your ass, Pae.

333
00:33:18,520 --> 00:33:19,960
Think about it.

334
00:33:20,800 --> 00:33:23,280
I did the governor a huge favor.

335
00:33:24,800 --> 00:33:27,880
So who do you think becomes
the next Village Chief

336
00:33:27,960 --> 00:33:29,440
of Khuan Phra-ngam,

337
00:33:30,120 --> 00:33:31,360
if not me?

338
00:33:37,760 --> 00:33:40,760
Brother, we're fugitives now.

339
00:33:40,840 --> 00:33:42,640
We can't stay here anymore.

340
00:33:44,480 --> 00:33:46,960
You want to become a disciple
at Khao Phrom, don't you?

341
00:33:47,560 --> 00:33:48,480
What do you want me to do?

342
00:33:49,080 --> 00:33:51,480
If you help me capture him
and hand him over to the authorities,

343
00:33:51,560 --> 00:33:53,640
you'll earn merit and recognition.

344
00:33:53,720 --> 00:33:55,160
Then I'll tell the governor

345
00:33:55,680 --> 00:33:58,560
to send you to Khao Phrom immediately.

346
00:33:58,640 --> 00:34:00,400
Everything that happened

347
00:34:00,480 --> 00:34:02,720
is because of your stupidity.

348
00:34:03,920 --> 00:34:05,320
He used me.

349
00:34:06,040 --> 00:34:08,400
He made me and Dad the scapegoats.

350
00:34:09,120 --> 00:34:10,400
I warned you.

351
00:34:11,159 --> 00:34:12,520
You never listen.

352
00:34:13,560 --> 00:34:16,719
Pud is slippery,
scheming 100 ways at once.

353
00:34:16,800 --> 00:34:18,120
How could you trust him?

354
00:34:19,679 --> 00:34:20,719
Nui.

355
00:34:22,719 --> 00:34:24,199
before I leave this town,

356
00:34:25,639 --> 00:34:26,880
there's something I have to do.

357
00:34:39,520 --> 00:34:41,960
- Is this bracelet pretty?
- It is.

358
00:34:42,040 --> 00:34:44,239
But that one's mine.

359
00:35:07,960 --> 00:35:08,800
Hey!

360
00:35:09,320 --> 00:35:10,160
Hey.

361
00:35:10,240 --> 00:35:11,520
If you don't want your child to die,

362
00:35:11,600 --> 00:35:13,120
shut up.

363
00:35:13,200 --> 00:35:14,400
Let my daughter go.

364
00:35:14,480 --> 00:35:17,800
I will. But you do exactly what I say.

365
00:35:22,320 --> 00:35:23,840
Don't give in to him, Father.

366
00:35:23,920 --> 00:35:26,440
Fine. I'll do it.

367
00:35:28,800 --> 00:35:30,400
I'll do whatever you want.

368
00:35:32,440 --> 00:35:35,320
Write the letter sending me
to become a disciple at Khao Phrom.

369
00:35:35,400 --> 00:35:36,880
Then I'll release your daughter.

370
00:35:53,840 --> 00:35:55,160
Hurry up.

371
00:36:12,240 --> 00:36:15,920
I did what you wanted.
Now let my daughter go.

372
00:36:25,400 --> 00:36:28,840
Call it payment for Pud using me.

373
00:36:41,360 --> 00:36:44,520
You pathetic thief! I'll hunt you down!

374
00:36:56,960 --> 00:36:58,280
You idiot!

375
00:36:58,880 --> 00:37:01,520
You caught him.

376
00:37:01,600 --> 00:37:04,040
How the hell
did you let him escape the cell?

377
00:37:04,120 --> 00:37:06,200
The police reported

378
00:37:06,280 --> 00:37:08,840
someone set a fire
and helped him escape, sir.

379
00:37:08,920 --> 00:37:10,680
Is that so?

380
00:37:10,760 --> 00:37:11,800
Father!

381
00:37:11,880 --> 00:37:14,360
- Father!
- Your Excellency.

382
00:37:14,440 --> 00:37:15,800
- Are you alright?
- Your Excellency?

383
00:37:16,880 --> 00:37:18,320
And that's why he dared come here,

384
00:37:18,400 --> 00:37:20,200
pull my whiskers right in my own house,

385
00:37:20,280 --> 00:37:22,000
and take my daughter hostage.

386
00:37:22,080 --> 00:37:25,360
I'll order the police
to hunt him down immediately, sir.

387
00:37:25,960 --> 00:37:28,760
By now, that worthless thief has probably
fled to the ends of the earth.

388
00:37:29,400 --> 00:37:32,360
It's strange.
He didn't take any money or valuables.

389
00:37:32,440 --> 00:37:35,400
He only wanted that letter from Father.

390
00:37:37,480 --> 00:37:38,720
A letter?

391
00:37:39,840 --> 00:37:41,120
What letter, sir?

392
00:37:41,880 --> 00:37:43,000
Tim,

393
00:37:43,680 --> 00:37:45,920
send men to intercept him at Khao Phrom.

394
00:37:47,840 --> 00:37:48,800
Yes, sir.

395
00:38:16,920 --> 00:38:17,880
Orror.

396
00:38:24,640 --> 00:38:25,720
Wait for me, Orror.

397
00:38:25,800 --> 00:38:26,880
Orror.

398
00:38:30,040 --> 00:38:31,000
Orror.

399
00:38:37,600 --> 00:38:38,560
Orror.

400
00:38:50,840 --> 00:38:52,400
Why did you bring me here?

401
00:38:54,160 --> 00:38:55,120
Blur,

402
00:38:55,640 --> 00:38:57,480
do you love me?

403
00:39:00,320 --> 00:39:01,240
Of course.

404
00:39:02,000 --> 00:39:03,280
How much?

405
00:39:05,160 --> 00:39:06,520
As much as my life.

406
00:39:08,640 --> 00:39:11,080
If you love me as much as your life,

407
00:39:12,680 --> 00:39:14,720
then you have to die for me.

408
00:39:26,040 --> 00:39:26,920
Orror.

409
00:39:29,960 --> 00:39:30,800
Orror…

410
00:39:32,440 --> 00:39:33,320
Why?

411
00:39:34,560 --> 00:39:37,000
Pay for what you did to me.

412
00:40:07,000 --> 00:40:08,240
He's awake, Master.

413
00:40:27,000 --> 00:40:28,240
Slowly.

414
00:40:43,040 --> 00:40:47,280
<i>Phutthang chivitang</i>
<i>yawa nippanang saranang katchami.</i>

415
00:41:00,520 --> 00:41:01,680
Where is this place?

416
00:41:02,760 --> 00:41:03,880
Khao Phrom.

417
00:41:03,960 --> 00:41:06,240
Master brought you here.

418
00:41:31,600 --> 00:41:33,920
My whole family is dead.

419
00:41:40,520 --> 00:41:42,360
Why am I still alive?

420
00:41:46,320 --> 00:41:49,680
It must be because
of that wild boar tusk you're wearing.

421
00:41:49,760 --> 00:41:51,160
That's why you survived.

422
00:42:00,720 --> 00:42:02,360
It's not because of any tusk.

423
00:42:04,920 --> 00:42:07,040
Your time has not yet come.

424
00:42:07,760 --> 00:42:08,960
By the merit of your past deeds,

425
00:42:09,720 --> 00:42:12,720
using medical knowledge
to treat the sick and the injured,

426
00:42:13,440 --> 00:42:16,080
neither can water drown you,
nor can fire burn you.

427
00:42:28,800 --> 00:42:30,280
You know…

428
00:42:31,920 --> 00:42:33,480
Nothing can be hidden

429
00:42:33,560 --> 00:42:35,880
from Old Master Khrua Phut.

430
00:43:33,800 --> 00:43:35,240
What's your name?

431
00:43:37,960 --> 00:43:39,200
My name is Yiam.

432
00:43:40,640 --> 00:43:42,240
I'm from Khuan Phra-ngam.

433
00:43:44,320 --> 00:43:45,760
My father was the village chief,

434
00:43:49,720 --> 00:43:51,920
but bandits killed my whole family.

435
00:43:57,000 --> 00:43:59,000
Master treated you until you survived.

436
00:43:59,920 --> 00:44:01,840
You have great merit, Yiam.

437
00:44:08,960 --> 00:44:10,480
But how did I get here?

438
00:44:12,160 --> 00:44:14,040
Doesn't it take days

439
00:44:14,560 --> 00:44:16,400
to travel to Khao Phrom?

440
00:44:17,440 --> 00:44:19,200
This is Khao Phrom, young man.

441
00:44:19,800 --> 00:44:21,520
Master is the one who brought you here.

442
00:44:33,120 --> 00:44:34,600
If I'd listened to my father…

443
00:44:35,680 --> 00:44:37,960
if I'd come to learn sorcery
at Khao Phrom from the start…

444
00:44:41,960 --> 00:44:45,360
my family wouldn't have been
slaughtered so brutally like this.

445
00:44:47,960 --> 00:44:51,720
Let it go. No power is greater than karma.

446
00:44:52,880 --> 00:44:54,720
You survived. That is already enough.

447
00:44:56,200 --> 00:44:58,360
Make use of the life you have left.

448
00:45:10,640 --> 00:45:13,320
The life I have left has only one purpose…

449
00:45:17,560 --> 00:45:18,920
revenge.

450
00:45:36,680 --> 00:45:37,640
Nui,

451
00:45:38,200 --> 00:45:40,360
this is it. Now I can go
learn sorcery at Khao Phrom.

452
00:45:40,440 --> 00:45:43,760
Will they send the police to arrest us?

453
00:45:44,960 --> 00:45:46,240
Then I'll expose everything,

454
00:45:46,320 --> 00:45:48,800
how they manipulated Bandit Pud
into killing Khun Yod.

455
00:45:50,000 --> 00:45:52,280
But you'll get dragged down too.

456
00:45:52,360 --> 00:45:53,760
Then let it all burn.

457
00:45:54,800 --> 00:45:56,480
I'm not suffering alone.

458
00:45:58,800 --> 00:46:01,160
I'm afraid they'll send someone
to silence us first.

459
00:46:02,960 --> 00:46:06,760
Once I learn sorcery at Khao Phrom,
I'll have skills of my own.

460
00:46:07,880 --> 00:46:09,240
And I'll protect you.

461
00:46:11,680 --> 00:46:14,640
As long as I'm with you,
I'm not afraid of anything.

462
00:46:15,440 --> 00:46:16,360
Alright.

463
00:46:25,200 --> 00:46:26,240
Dad.

464
00:46:40,240 --> 00:46:41,800
Chum Suea is finished.

465
00:46:41,880 --> 00:46:43,040
Huh?

466
00:46:47,400 --> 00:46:49,040
So there must be a traitor among us.

467
00:46:50,280 --> 00:46:51,360
That damned Chum, Dad.

468
00:46:52,360 --> 00:46:53,800
He must've leaked our secret.

469
00:46:55,320 --> 00:46:56,920
Filthy bastard.

470
00:46:58,360 --> 00:46:59,720
And what about Yiwha?

471
00:46:59,800 --> 00:47:01,160
How are Yiwha and the others?

472
00:47:02,000 --> 00:47:05,640
I had Niem take Yiwha
to stay with Chaem at Huai Yao.

473
00:47:05,720 --> 00:47:07,320
Those who survived

474
00:47:08,960 --> 00:47:10,760
scattered and resettled elsewhere.

475
00:47:19,360 --> 00:47:20,280
Dad…

476
00:47:31,040 --> 00:47:32,200
About Khun Yod's death…

477
00:47:32,280 --> 00:47:33,600
Don't say anything.

478
00:47:34,600 --> 00:47:36,280
Whatever you saw, whatever you know,

479
00:47:37,000 --> 00:47:38,040
keep quiet.

480
00:47:41,320 --> 00:47:42,600
Yod is dead.

481
00:47:43,880 --> 00:47:46,080
It must've been Duang's doing.

482
00:47:47,000 --> 00:47:48,840
But they pushed the blame onto me and you.

483
00:47:54,840 --> 00:47:59,000
You came to see us, so that means
you've forgiven Lasor already, right?

484
00:48:02,280 --> 00:48:03,480
My Chum Suea

485
00:48:04,280 --> 00:48:06,920
was destroyed, just like
Grandma Chi Pa Khao foretold.

486
00:48:08,880 --> 00:48:10,560
My brothers and sisters

487
00:48:11,400 --> 00:48:14,640
were wounded and slaughtered.
We lost the ones we loved.

488
00:48:16,640 --> 00:48:18,840
Now we're wandering
with nowhere to lay our heads.

489
00:48:28,440 --> 00:48:29,840
I'm sorry, Dad,

490
00:48:30,680 --> 00:48:32,800
that I wasn't there
to help you protect our Chum Suea.

491
00:48:40,880 --> 00:48:43,880
There's something
I want you to do to atone.

492
00:48:45,520 --> 00:48:46,520
Of course, Dad.

493
00:48:47,520 --> 00:48:48,600
Tell me.

494
00:48:49,360 --> 00:48:51,120
I'll do anything you say.

495
00:48:53,480 --> 00:48:54,640
Ordain.

496
00:48:57,160 --> 00:48:58,480
And never disrobe.

497
00:49:11,720 --> 00:49:12,800
Why, Dad?

498
00:49:13,600 --> 00:49:14,440
If you ordain,

499
00:49:15,920 --> 00:49:19,280
I'll forget everything you've done

500
00:49:21,520 --> 00:49:22,560
and I'll consider…

501
00:49:25,040 --> 00:49:27,480
my son reborn in saffron robes.

502
00:49:29,760 --> 00:49:31,120
Can you do that for me?

503
00:49:52,000 --> 00:49:54,440
Whoa. They put a bounty

504
00:49:54,520 --> 00:49:57,280
on Bandit Wad and his son,
100 <i>tamlueng</i> each.

505
00:50:02,480 --> 00:50:05,720
WANTED

506
00:50:07,040 --> 00:50:07,920
WANTED
BANDIT WAD

507
00:50:08,000 --> 00:50:09,840
WANTED
LASOR

508
00:50:13,080 --> 00:50:16,480
Well, they're the ones who robbed and
slaughtered that whole family last night.

509
00:50:17,160 --> 00:50:20,120
Heartless bastards.
Catch them and hang them both.

510
00:50:20,200 --> 00:50:23,240
- Yes.
- Right.

511
00:50:23,840 --> 00:50:24,880
No.

512
00:50:27,600 --> 00:50:31,120
- They look brutal.
- They are heartless.

513
00:50:31,200 --> 00:50:32,720
They deserve to be caught.

514
00:51:47,240 --> 00:51:48,640
Don't worry.

515
00:51:50,360 --> 00:51:52,200
I'll avenge you.

516
00:52:12,960 --> 00:52:15,080
When I ask, "Manusso si?"

517
00:52:15,160 --> 00:52:17,920
You answer, "Ama, bhante."

518
00:52:21,200 --> 00:52:23,160
Alright, let's start.

519
00:52:24,120 --> 00:52:25,640
<i>Manusso si?</i>

520
00:52:34,000 --> 00:52:35,440
I don't want to ordain.

521
00:52:38,440 --> 00:52:39,680
Just do it.

522
00:52:40,280 --> 00:52:42,320
Father Wad will forgive you.

523
00:52:46,080 --> 00:52:48,040
But I'd have to stay ordained for life.

524
00:52:49,920 --> 00:52:52,760
That's good. You'll become the abbot.

525
00:52:54,480 --> 00:52:55,320
Nui.

526
00:53:04,800 --> 00:53:06,640
And if you don't ordain,

527
00:53:08,000 --> 00:53:09,160
what will you do?

528
00:53:20,760 --> 00:53:22,520
I'm going to Khao Phrom to study.

529
00:53:24,680 --> 00:53:26,320
At least if I learn sorcery,

530
00:53:28,120 --> 00:53:29,640
I can get revenge on those bastards,

531
00:53:30,680 --> 00:53:32,240
for what they did to me,

532
00:53:33,200 --> 00:53:34,920
what they did to my father's Chum Suea.

533
00:53:40,400 --> 00:53:42,480
But Father Wad wants you to ordain.

534
00:53:43,080 --> 00:53:45,640
That means he doesn't want you
to walk the same road as him.

535
00:53:46,440 --> 00:53:47,880
Stop thinking about revenge

536
00:53:48,400 --> 00:53:50,400
and come back to chanting
the ordination responses with me.

537
00:53:51,400 --> 00:53:52,480
Please.

538
00:54:20,600 --> 00:54:24,160
I probably won't ever see you again, Blur.

539
00:54:43,360 --> 00:54:45,360
If you two have fate together,

540
00:54:45,440 --> 00:54:47,840
one day you'll meet again.

541
00:54:51,160 --> 00:54:52,720
I've let go, Uncle.

542
00:54:53,600 --> 00:54:57,200
In this life, I don't think
I'll dare love anyone again.

543
00:54:58,480 --> 00:55:00,240
I'm afraid of parting again.

544
00:55:10,960 --> 00:55:11,800
In life,

545
00:55:12,400 --> 00:55:14,200
if you're meant for each other,
you'll end up together.

546
00:55:15,480 --> 00:55:16,680
Look at you.

547
00:55:17,360 --> 00:55:19,840
Your father arranged a bond and all that,

548
00:55:19,920 --> 00:55:21,600
it still turned out like this.

549
00:55:28,360 --> 00:55:30,520
Anyway, for now,

550
00:55:30,600 --> 00:55:33,600
stay quiet.
Don't go stirring trouble anywhere.

551
00:55:40,080 --> 00:55:41,000
Uncle,

552
00:55:41,520 --> 00:55:44,080
what happened to Dad's friend, Yod?

553
00:55:46,040 --> 00:55:47,360
They slaughtered his whole family.

554
00:55:48,040 --> 00:55:49,480
Not a single one survived.

555
00:55:50,680 --> 00:55:52,440
His son too.

556
00:55:53,640 --> 00:55:55,640
Your father was going to
have you marry that son.

557
00:55:57,520 --> 00:55:59,400
Who killed them, Uncle?

558
00:56:06,280 --> 00:56:09,080
Even now, no one can pin it on anybody.

559
00:56:10,600 --> 00:56:15,120
I feel for your father,
being hunted by the authorities.

560
00:56:15,200 --> 00:56:16,480
They accused him of being the murderer.

561
00:56:17,880 --> 00:56:20,480
How could he kill
a friend he swore brotherhood with?

562
00:56:20,560 --> 00:56:22,480
That would break
the oath of our Chum Suea.

563
00:56:24,440 --> 00:56:26,760
No one knows how deep your father and Yod
loved each other,

564
00:56:26,840 --> 00:56:28,680
like they'd die for one another.

565
00:56:29,560 --> 00:56:31,760
Only me and Chaem know.

566
00:56:34,640 --> 00:56:36,920
I'm going to find the real killer

567
00:56:37,000 --> 00:56:39,040
and clear my father's name.

568
00:56:47,320 --> 00:56:50,120
<i>Is that the spirit</i>
<i>of my father, my mother,</i>

569
00:56:50,200 --> 00:56:52,040
and my little sister, Master?

570
00:56:52,120 --> 00:56:55,920
Everything arises, exists, and ceases.

571
00:56:56,000 --> 00:56:56,840
Who are you here for?

572
00:56:59,800 --> 00:57:01,400
Just think of this place as your home.

573
00:57:01,480 --> 00:57:03,640
<i>Who's that woman? She's pretty.</i>

574
00:57:04,160 --> 00:57:05,520
She's cute.

575
00:57:05,600 --> 00:57:06,480
Who the hell are you?

576
00:57:09,520 --> 00:57:11,600
Don't go to Khao Phrom.

577
00:57:11,680 --> 00:57:13,040
Even if you go,

578
00:57:13,800 --> 00:57:16,840
it's not like they'll teach you sorcery.

579
00:57:17,440 --> 00:57:19,000
You think I don't dare?

580
00:57:23,000 --> 00:57:24,400
I've sent my men to hunt him down.

581
00:57:24,480 --> 00:57:26,760
<i>If they can't take him alive, kill him.</i>

582
00:57:27,960 --> 00:57:29,160
You won't get away now.

583
00:58:14,880 --> 00:58:16,840
Subtitles translation by:
Panuwat Baikeawon
